The paper deals with a clustering problem in a metric space, which is a common topic in computer science. The use of a data structure to maintain a solution suggests that the paper may belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The problem of minimizing the sum of radii involves distance metrics, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions the use of competitive analysis, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the dynamic nature of the problem suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SI).
